Model Building: Logistic Regression¶

In [33]:
#Basic Logistic Regression

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression, LinearRegression
from sklearn import metrics

logreg = LogisticRegression()
logreg.fit(X_train,y_train)

y_pred_train = logreg.predict(X_train)
print("Train Accuracy : {}".format(metrics.accuracy_score(y_train, y_pred_train)))
print("Train Precision : {}".format(metrics.precision_score(y_train, y_pred_train)))
print("Train Sensitivity/Recall : {}".format(metrics.recall_score(y_train, y_pred_train)))
print("Train AOC : {}".format(metrics.roc_auc_score(y_train, y_pred_train)))
print("Train F1 : {}".format(metrics.f1_score(y_train, y_pred_train)))
print("Train Confusion Matrix :")
print(metrics.confusion_matrix(y_train, y_pred_train))


y_pred = logreg.predict(X_test)
print("Test Accuracy : {}".format(metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)))
print("Test Precision : {}".format(metrics.precision_score(y_test, y_pred)))
print("Test Sensitivity/Recall : {}".format(metrics.recall_score(y_test, y_pred)))
print("Test AOC : {}".format(metrics.roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred)))
print("Test F1 : {}".format(metrics.f1_score(y_test, y_pred)))
print("Test Confusion Matrix :")
print(metrics.confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))

coefficients = pd.concat([pd.DataFrame(X_train.columns,columns = ["column"]),pd.DataFrame(np.transpose(logreg.coef_),columns = ["coef_val"])], axis = 1)
coefficients.coef_val = coefficients.coef_val.abs()
print(coefficients.sort_values(by = ['coef_val'],ascending = False).head(10))
print("\n")
